@startuml Hybrid STM32 Raspberry Pi Configuration

title Hybrid: STM32 → Raspberry Pi → STM32 (Zephyr + Linux + Zephyr)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam ArrowColor #444441
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<stm32>> #EEEDFE
    BorderColor<<stm32>> #534AB7
    FontColor<<stm32>> #26215C

    BackgroundColor<<rpi>> #E1F5EE
    BorderColor<<rpi>> #0F6E56
    FontColor<<rpi>> #04342C

    BackgroundColor<<bus>> #FAEEDA
    BorderColor<<bus>> #BA7517
    FontColor<<bus>> #412402

    BackgroundColor<<ethernet>> #E1F5EE
    BorderColor<<ethernet>> #0F6E56
    FontColor<<ethernet>> #04342C
}

'--- STM32 #1 (Source) ---
package "STM32 #1\n(Zephyr RTOS)" <<stm32>> {
    component [CAN1 TX\nt₀: send] as STM1_TX <<stm32>>
    component [CAN2 RX\nt₃: receive] as STM1_RX <<stm32>>
}

'--- Raspberry Pi (Gateway) ---
package "Raspberry Pi\n(Linux)" <<rpi>> {
    component [CAN HAT RX] as RPI_CAN <<rpi>>
    component [Linux Open1722\nEncapsulate] as RPI_ENC <<rpi>>
    component [Ethernet TX] as RPI_ETH <<rpi>>
}

'--- STM32 #2 (Gateway) ---
package "STM32 #2\n(Zephyr RTOS)" <<stm32>> {
    component [Ethernet RX\n+ LAN8720 PHY] as STM2_ETH <<stm32>>
    component [Zephyr Open1722\nDecapsulate] as STM2_DEC <<stm32>>
    component [CAN1 TX] as STM2_CAN <<stm32>>
}

'--- Buses ---
component [CAN Bus A\n250 kbps] as CANA <<bus>>
component [CAN Bus B\n250 kbps] as CANB <<bus>>
component [Ethernet\nDirect Cable\nIEEE-1722] as ETH <<ethernet>>

'--- Flow ---
STM1_TX --> CANA : t₀
CANA --> RPI_CAN
RPI_CAN --> RPI_ENC
RPI_ENC --> RPI_ETH
RPI_ETH --> ETH : IEEE-1722\nAVTP
ETH --> STM2_ETH
STM2_ETH --> STM2_DEC
STM2_DEC --> STM2_CAN
STM2_CAN --> CANB
CANB --> STM1_RX : t₃

note bottom of RPI_ENC
    **Asymmetric Gateway Test**
    Linux encapsulation vs
    Zephyr decapsulation
    Identifies bottleneck
end note

@enduml
